</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{toha}}}} indicates a word or phrase that is being defined.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      UN@EM{{@HI{{toha}}}},@KJ{{country^take*along}}@HI{{nokotodesu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      "UN" refers to the United Nations.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{toha}}}} is used between two clauses that are opposed in meaning, the first clause representing a concession to the second.
In this case it usually appears in the form @EM{{@HI{{tohaie}}}}. The meaning is "though" or "even though".

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{springtime}}@EM{{tohaie}}mada@KJ{{cold}}i.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Even though it's spiring, it's still cold.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

